        <num>CCP 2130</num>
        <heading>2130.  Record on appeal; statement of facts</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2130.  Record on appeal; statement of facts
A party may require the clerk to cause the testimony to be taken down in writing and this transcript shall serve as the statement of facts of the case.  The parties may agree to a narrative of the facts in accordance with the provisions of Article 2131.</p>
        </content>
